    "client_msg_id": "4ab8615d-6ae7-4ab2-ac35-84a011aaa9c2",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Perhaps what interested me is more the general notion that languages have a 'culture' surrounding them.\nThe article does indeed make some sweeping generalizations and the idea that that culture is directly reducable to language constructs is questionable.\nWhether or not culture is contingent(if at all) on the language constructs, it does seem to be an important part of it's 'design'.\nIndeed, if the differences between constructs are practically negligable, then isn't it exactly culture or 'aesthetic sense' that differentiates languages?",
    "user": "UAJ9DV971",
